public class Name
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Name>

A Name class has a Name object consisting first name/last name pair, which both first name and last name are of String objects.

compareTo

public int compareTo(Name theName)
Compares names to see if one is alphabetically before, after, or identical as the other. The last name is the prior determinant, and the first name is the secondary determinant to compare.

Specified by:
compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Name>
Parameters:
theName - The given name used to compare.
Returns:
Returns a negative value if the given name is alphabetically before the name being compared to. Returns a positive value if the given name is alphabetically after the name being compared to. Returns the value 0 if the given name is identical to the name being compared to.
